post_text:
Welcome back to our School Families and Amazing Staff for the start of a truly one-of-a-kind year! This is certainly not what any of us expected; but by working together, we'll be able to overcome any challenges that come our way.

No doubt, today will have it's own "hiccups." We ask for your patience and understanding as we work through them. We will do our best to help direct any questions our parents have to the right staff members who can help as quickly as we can.

Regardless of the situations we find ourselves in, today is a great day to learn! We're glad you're with us to do so.

post_text:
At today's press briefing, Governor Murphy announced that face coverings will be required for all students at all times inside school buildings.

In addition, the New Jersey Department of Education is preparing a FAQ regarding reopening plans.

As we mentioned before - while we have plans regarding reopening - they will have to change when we receive additional guidance from agencies like the New Jersey Department of Education. We will do our best to share these changes with our school families as soon as they become available.
shared_text:
Governor Phil Murphy
August 3 at 1:11 PM ·

UPDATE: Face coverings will be required for all students at all times while inside a school building, regardless of social distancing, unless doing so would inhibit the individual’s health.

The updated guidance from the New Jersey Department of Education on face coverings for students will also include several exceptions to this standard including an exception for certain students with disabilities.

Additionally, the Department is sharing its checklist of specific items that its country offices of education will use to ensure that district plans meet our guidelines.

The Department is also currently finalizing a FAQ document about reopening plans.

post_text:
Per guidance from the State of New Jersey, the Pennsauken School District is planning for an A/B Split Schedule for the upcoming 2020/2021 School Year. **The days the students are home will be a working school day as well, based off what they learned the day before in school.**

Families will receive letters from their principals the week of July 26, informing them of their children's assigned schedules, so that they can make the necessary accommodations. **Siblings will be scheduled on the same day.** To download a PDF of the schedule, visit https://www.pennsauken.net/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=437124&type=d

We've been hard at work to prepare for our students returning in September. The District is planning to release a video overview of our plans for the upcoming school year on or around Friday, July 24. You'll be able to view it here, as well as on our website and Pennsauken Television.

post_text:
As of April 7, 2020, Governor Murphy has ordered the indefinite closure of all New Jersey Schools. Due to this direction from the state government, our schools will operate on this current remote learning process until further notice.

Pennsauken Public Schools will be observing spring break beginning April 10, 2020. Therefore there will not be remote learning from April 10th through the 17th. Students will return to remote learning Monday April 20, 2020, through the remainder of the semester.
text:
As of April 7, 2020, Governor Murphy has ordered the indefinite closure of all New Jersey Schools. Due to this direction from the state government, our schools will operate on this current remote learning process until further notice.

Pennsauken Public Schools will be observing spring break beginning April 10, 2020. Therefore there will not be remote learning from April 10th through the 17th. Students will return to remote learning Monday April 20, 2020, through the remainder of the semester.

post_text:
As we prepare for Spring Break, we hope that you enjoy the time off with your family. We thank all of our staff who are going above and beyond during this unprecedented time in education. We also applaud the hard work of parents, guardians, grandparents, siblings, etc. as they help students with their lessons.

Today, we made the difficult decision to cancel this year's PHS senior trip. We are just as disappointed as our students. This is not what anyone wanted and we hope that you understand how necessary this decision was.

As long as Governor Murphy's Executive Order #104 is in effect, we cannot allow students back into our schools. Plans have been already been in the works to resume remote learning on April 20. More details will be provided soon.

Please stay safe. Working together, we'll get through this.

post_text:
Join us on Sunday, March 29, for the first annual Sauken Speed 5k, 1 Mile Fun Run, and Kid's 400m Dash!

Held at Pennsauken High School, this flat and fast 5k course and 1 Mile Fun Run starts and finishes on the brand new track in the recently updated Vince McAneney Stadium. Your kids can compete in the Kid's 400m Dash, and then let them participate in some fun games and activities on the stadium turf (organized by Pennsauken HS Honor Society students) while you compete in the 5k race or 1 Mile Fun Run.

Proceeds from the race will go to support various programs such as the LilleyStrong Foundation, support for Pennsauken High School student Amanda Lezcano's recovery from Guillain-Barré Syndrome, and the Pennsauken High School Cross Country program.

https://runsignup.com/Race/NJ/Pennsauken/SaukenSpeed5kKidsFunRun?rsus=100-200-8a846374-84c0-4f39-8b57-70ff52ca599d

post_text:
Congratulations to Rachel Biehl, Samantha Marino, and Azarya Patterson, the Pennsauken students who won this year's Pennsauken Township Holiday Parade Poster Contest, sponsored by the Pennsauken-Merchantville Area Chamber Of Commerce PMAC! As the first place winner, Azarya's artwork is highlighted in this year's poster for the Pennsauken Township Holiday Parade!

A special thank you to art teachers Mrs. Ford and Mrs. Bennett, without whom, this contest would not be possible.

The Pennsauken Holiday Parade is held this Saturday, Nov. 30, at 1:00 p.m. along Westfield Ave.! Come out and celebrate the kick off of the holiday season!
